and we should be...

23:58.404 --> 24:00.702
everything running normal.

24:00.704 --> 24:03.037
- Okay, so one more
announcement.

24:03.038 --> 24:05.738
We have to be extremely careful

24:05.740 --> 24:06.770
what we do to the system.

24:06.970 --> 24:08.471
I mean, we know that anybody

24:08.472 --> 24:10.770
who's even updating
a number somewhere

24:10.771 --> 24:13.570
might stop our system for
more than an hour quite easily.

24:13.571 --> 24:17.204
So please be absolutely sure
that you yourself

24:17.205 --> 24:19.737
and everybody in your system
is not touching the system,

24:19.738 --> 24:23.037
unless it's been agreed
by the shift leader, yeah?

24:23.039 --> 24:26.206
Nothing should be touched, yeah?

24:26.207 --> 24:27.639
And that includes all things

24:27.640 --> 24:29.105
that you're absolutely
dead certain

24:29.106 --> 24:30.790
they will not do anything wrong.

24:31.771 --> 24:33.106
Especially those things.

24:34.872 --> 24:38.603
- It's being called the
largest scientific experiment

24:38.604 --> 24:40.105
in history,

24:40.106 --> 24:43.038
and some say
one that could cause Armageddon.

24:43.039 --> 24:45.372
- It's the strangest
experiment ever:

24:45.373 --> 24:47.272
mankind's most ambitious attempt

24:47.273 --> 24:50.407
to understand
how we all got here.

24:52.240 --> 24:54.639
- Thousands of scientists
from around the world

24:54.640 --> 24:58.238
spent 20 years designing
an extraordinary machine.

24:58.239 --> 25:02.771
It cost £5 billion
and will switching on very soon.

25:02.772 --> 25:04.873
This is a genesis machine,

25:04.874 --> 25:06.141
a window on creation.

25:11.206 --> 25:14.140
Five months of testing on...

25:17.214 --> 25:20.107
- They're looking for something
called the God Particle,

25:20.108 --> 25:22.540
but skeptics are saying nobody
knows what will happen

25:22.541 --> 25:24.275
when they turn on the switch.

25:24.276 --> 25:27.207
