What we're going to see today

26:14.241 --> 26:17.908
is the launch
of the first beam of protons

26:17.909 --> 26:20.409
around this enormous ring.

26:21.943 --> 26:25.408
Very shortly, Lyn Evans,
the project director,

26:25.409 --> 26:28.074
is going to be addressing
CERN staff,

26:28.075 --> 26:30.108
who are gathered
at different points

26:30.109 --> 26:33.475
around this massive complex.

26:33.476 --> 26:39.309
- It's just the first glimpse
at the fact the machine can run.

26:39.310 --> 26:40.877
I mean, so what you need,
really,

26:40.878 --> 26:42.576
is, you need two beams
colliding together

26:42.578 --> 26:44.276
for quite a few...

26:44.277 --> 26:46.209
quite a long period of time
before you calculate,

26:46.210 --> 26:47.743
get enough...

26:47.744 --> 26:50.443
sufficient statistics
in which to actually

26:50.444 --> 26:52.576
be able to look
for the new physics.

26:52.577 --> 26:54.643
But single beam,
the first beam, isn't even that.

26:54.644 --> 26:56.277
You're not even getting
any collisions.

26:56.278 --> 26:58.744
It's just one beam
going around in a circle,

26:58.745 --> 27:00.409
not even at the high energies.

27:00.410 --> 27:02.376
Just one beam going
around in the low energy circle,

27:02.377 --> 27:04.544
that sort of says, "Okay,
we made it around the ring once

27:04.545 --> 27:05.576
for the first time."

27:05.777 --> 27:07.311
And it's a huge event.

27:07.312 --> 27:09.311
Right, after 19 years,
you've been waiting

27:09.312 --> 27:10.975
for this first step.

27:10.976 --> 27:12.709
Let's get started, everybody.

27:12.711 --> 27:15.643
Now comes the day of reckoning.

27:15.644 --> 27:19.810
Five, four, three,

27:19.811 --> 27:22.743
two, one...

27:22.744 --> 27:25.143
Now.

27:25.144 --> 27:26.644
No beam.

27:28.610 --> 27:30.076
Yeah.

27:30.077 --> 27:33.977
So where are we
with the injection kicker?

27:33.978 --> 27:36.812
Oh, well...
they're out.

27:36.813 --> 27:39.811
Okay, never mind.

27:39.812 --> 27:41.310
Let's go.

27:41.311 --> 27:45.077
Five, four, three,

27:45.078 --> 27:49.245
two, one, zero.

27:56.746 --> 27:58.311
We get a beam on this pulse?

27:58.311 --> 28:00.646
I hope so.

28:13.481 --> 28:13.979
Yes!

