This is timing, in nanoseconds,

28:49.982 --> 28:51.815
which we knew
from the cosmic data.

28:51.816 --> 28:53.948
- That is very nice.
- Yes.

28:53.949 --> 28:56.379
- Upstairs, I think people
were more excited about this.

28:56.380 --> 28:59.146
- If you're in Google,
that means... that's the world.

28:59.147 --> 29:01.047
This is the most important thing
today.

29:01.048 --> 29:02.314
This is the first,

29:02.315 --> 29:03.648
and this tells us
a lot of things.

29:03.649 --> 29:05.313
It tells us that
the magnetic properties

29:05.314 --> 29:06.613
of the machine are good,

29:06.614 --> 29:08.313
that the aperture is clear.

29:08.314 --> 29:10.780
There's nothing is sticking into
the beam pipe anywhere.

29:10.781 --> 29:14.814
So a very, very encouraging sign
and remarkable progress.

29:14.815 --> 29:16.714
- Did you guys see
our beautiful plot?

29:16.715 --> 29:18.447
- What?
- Okay, I want to show you this.

29:18.647 --> 29:20.147
Come on, show them the plot.

29:20.148 --> 29:22.114
You can take a picture of...
here you go.

29:22.115 --> 29:24.481
Well, see if you can get it.

29:24.482 --> 29:25.815
I don't think
there's anyone else

29:25.816 --> 29:27.880
I can show my plot to, so...

29:27.882 --> 29:29.248
It worked.

29:29.249 --> 29:31.048
It just worked.

29:31.049 --> 29:33.315
And there are so few times
in life where it just works.

29:33.316 --> 29:35.715
And there are so
even fewer times in life

29:35.716 --> 29:38.549
where it just works great.

29:38.549 --> 29:39.816
We rocked.

29:39.816 --> 29:42.152
I mean, Tile, first beam...

29:44.151 --> 29:46.050
We destroyed that shit.

