They've had beams circulating
for a full 30 seconds.

29:52.049 --> 29:53.283
So let me understand.

29:53.284 --> 29:56.382
This is one beam going one way?

29:56.383 --> 29:58.148
- They have one beam
going one way,

29:58.149 --> 30:00.282
and then they went to the
other beam going the other way.

30:00.282 --> 30:01.387
Well, does it work?

30:01.587 --> 30:03.216
The second beam,
did it go fully around?

30:03.217 --> 30:05.449
- Everything...
- they both went around.

30:05.450 --> 30:07.649
I think
they had the beam go around

30:07.650 --> 30:08.915
about a million times.

30:08.916 --> 30:10.384
Something like that.

30:10.385 --> 30:13.782
- Yeah, their Twitter feed
said 10 million.

30:13.783 --> 30:17.783
- Now we'll become, you know,
CERN Twitter junkies.

30:21.218 --> 30:23.249
I guess this is exciting.

30:23.250 --> 30:26.949
My logical self
wants to be excited.

30:26.950 --> 30:31.397
My psychological self
is very cautious.

30:45.384 --> 30:47.149
My parents are both Iranian

30:47.151 --> 30:50.251
and both physicists,

30:50.252 --> 30:54.418
and my father in particular
had real political difficulties

30:54.419 --> 30:55.553
with the regime,

30:56.552 --> 30:59.418
and we had to go underground
for a number of years,

30:59.418 --> 31:02.653
and we ended up escaping
from Iran

31:02.654 --> 31:06.819
through the border of Turkey.

31:06.820 --> 31:11.418
But then, through
a number of wonderful accidents,

31:11.419 --> 31:13.218
we ended up in Canada.

31:13.219 --> 31:15.917
I got interested in physics

31:15.918 --> 31:17.918
when I was 13 or 14 years old.

31:17.919 --> 31:21.451
It just offered the way
to combine the two things

31:21.452 --> 31:22.952
I really loved:

31:22.953 --> 31:25.753
mathematics
and things in the natural world.

