31:45.418 --> 31:47.885
- Thinking about the LHC
has been the center

31:47.886 --> 31:53.584
of my intellectual life
for about 15, 16 years now.

31:53.585 --> 31:56.219
Depending on what happens
with the LHC,

31:56.220 --> 31:57.820
you know, these are 15 years

31:57.820 --> 31:59.952
I could come to see
as the best possible thing

31:59.953 --> 32:01.952
I could've been doing
with this time,

32:01.953 --> 32:04.653
or it could just be
that the entire 15 years

32:04.654 --> 32:06.053
might as well have not happened,

32:06.054 --> 32:07.653
had no impact,

32:07.654 --> 32:09.920
and then that's just 15 years
that are gone.

32:09.921 --> 32:11.289
It's not the sort of thing

32:11.488 --> 32:14.254
where there's
a consolation prize.

32:14.255 --> 32:18.788
You know,
it's a fairly binary situation.

32:18.789 --> 32:20.788
I definitely won't feel,
"Oh, well,

32:20.789 --> 32:22.621
"I gave it
a good old college try.

32:22.622 --> 32:23.887
"It's all fine anyway.

32:23.888 --> 32:25.120
It's just trying that counts."

32:25.121 --> 32:26.753
I don't believe that.

32:26.754 --> 32:28.320
I don't believe
it's just trying that counts.

32:28.321 --> 32:29.820
I believe getting it right
is what counts.

