01:17:38.013 --> 01:17:40.913
there's news that there's
going to be another announcement

01:17:40.914 --> 01:17:43.178
about the Higgs.

01:17:43.179 --> 01:17:44.913
I've heard tons of rumors,

01:17:44.914 --> 01:17:46.812
and I've heard
they're things on blogs,

01:17:46.813 --> 01:17:49.579
and there's already stuff
in the newspaper.

01:17:49.580 --> 01:17:52.177
- 18 hours or so
until the announcement,

01:17:52.178 --> 01:17:56.313
so I'm really looking forward
to what they're going to say,

01:17:56.314 --> 01:17:58.546
and I want to be there.

01:17:58.547 --> 01:18:01.179
Actually, I'm thinking
of going early in the morning,

01:18:01.180 --> 01:18:04.045
or I'll send
my young colleagues,

01:18:04.046 --> 01:18:09.413
who have more stamina to sit
and occupy a chair for me.

01:18:09.414 --> 01:18:12.178
It is July 3rd...

01:18:12.179 --> 01:18:15.048
the night of July 3, 2012,

01:18:15.049 --> 01:18:19.347
and I am driving to Princeton,
to the Institute,

01:18:19.348 --> 01:18:22.413
to hang out with Nima
and a big crowd,

01:18:22.414 --> 01:18:26.146
who are all staying up
until 3:00 in the morning

01:18:26.147 --> 01:18:30.547
because they're going to
present the Higgs data at CERN

01:18:30.548 --> 01:18:33.248
at 9:00 in the morning
Geneva time.

01:18:33.249 --> 01:18:35.381
Certainly the biggest thing
that's happened...

01:18:35.382 --> 01:18:37.748
the discovery
of new fundamental particles...

01:18:37.750 --> 01:18:39.346
in my lifetime.

01:18:39.347 --> 01:18:42.180
And the Higgs is a particle
like no other,

01:18:42.181 --> 01:18:44.380
like nothing
we've ever seen before,

01:18:44.381 --> 01:18:46.914
and it is weird,
and we do not understand it,

01:18:46.915 --> 01:18:50.246
but...

